The paper proposes a map matching algorithm based on machine learning techniques, specifically conditional random fields (CRF), which is a popular approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The algorithm also involves mining driver route preferences, which could fall under the category of data mining (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of temporal-spatial context, which could be relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
